1
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:48,550
Lin Hua, you're back.

2
00:00:50,880 --> 00:00:51,640
Sir,

3
00:00:52,240 --> 00:00:53,640
what happened to the dog?

4
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:55,440
It ate rat poison and died today.

5
00:00:56,520 --> 00:00:58,920
I just buried it,
but the rain washed it out.

6
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,920
I need to dig this pit a bit deeper.

7
00:03:10,310 --> 00:03:11,910
I was wrong! I was wrong!

8
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:13,620
Give back my shipyard!

9
00:03:13,630 --> 00:03:14,800
Give back my son!

10
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,800
Mr. Ma! Mr. Ma!

11
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:18,800
Mr. Ma, this won't do.

12
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,630
You'd get him killed, Mr. Ma.

13
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,150
Give back my shipyard!

14
00:03:22,150 --> 00:03:23,710
Give back my son!

15
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,520
S-spare my life!

16
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:27,560
Mr. Ma.

17
00:03:34,680 --> 00:03:37,000
Make sure to investigate
the cause of this explosion

18
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:37,960
thoroughly.

19
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,880
The cargo is overdue.

20
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:40,880
Notify...

21
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,150
the partner company.

22
00:03:43,360 --> 00:03:44,120
Okay.

23
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,960
Here, Mr. Ma. Watch your step.

24
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:43,950
Thank you, everyone.

25
00:04:46,720 --> 00:04:47,850
Let's go down first.

26
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,810
I'll turn myself in.

27
00:05:40,830 --> 00:05:41,760
If anyone should

28
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:44,909
turn themselves in, it's me.

29
00:05:45,830 --> 00:05:47,240
You're just a victim.

30
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,530
Whether the police find out or not,

31
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:55,550
Ma Kai's death

32
00:05:57,510 --> 00:05:59,040
has nothing to do with you.

33
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:04,360
We can't hide it.

34
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:05,800
We can't.

35
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:20,920
Let's go.

36
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,040
Xia Gang killed so many people.

37
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,560
How dare he come here?

38
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,360
It's all Xia Gang's fault.

39
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:46,360
You died so unjustly.

40
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:22,120
Mr. Ma,

41
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,360
except for you,

42
00:07:24,870 --> 00:07:27,750
the other twelve victims' families
have all signed.

43
00:07:27,750 --> 00:07:30,150
The reason no one
is making a scene right now

44
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:32,830
is that you're also a victim's family.

45
00:07:33,870 --> 00:07:34,390
So...

46
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,460
Have they found the cause?

47
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:42,450
The police are still investigating
the cause of the explosion.

48
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,000
Tell Manager Qiu

49
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,000
to appease the victims' families.

50
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,659
Make sure there's no trouble.

51
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:49,800
Okay.

52
00:07:50,870 --> 00:07:52,130
I'll take my leave now.

53
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,910
You should go back.

54
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,680
I want to be alone for a while.

55
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,730
Let me stay with you.

56
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:38,360
Alright, you go back and rest first.

57
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,320
I'll come get you for dinner.

58
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,440
Don't bother.

59
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:47,550
Lu, did you smell that?

60
00:13:47,550 --> 00:13:48,790
What is that smell?

61
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:52,840
It smells like something burning.

62
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,080
Xia Xue!

63
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:06,550
Xue!

64
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:08,800
What's wrong?

65
00:14:09,030 --> 00:14:09,750
What is that smell?

66
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,480
Lu Ming! Xue!

67
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:10,960
Xia Xue!

68
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:12,080
Liu!

69
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:13,080
Xia's house is on fire.

70
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:13,910
Hurry!

71
00:14:13,910 --> 00:14:14,670
Xia Xue!

72
00:14:14,670 --> 00:14:15,550
Hurry!

73
00:14:19,720 --> 00:14:20,550
Xia Xue!

74
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,150
Xia Xue!

75
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,910
Xia Xue! Xia Xue.

76
00:14:39,550 --> 00:14:41,080
Fire! Help!

77
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,080
Fire! Help!

78
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:45,790
Fire!

79
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:48,080
Fire!

80
00:14:49,790 --> 00:14:51,440
Fire! Help!

81
00:14:51,670 --> 00:14:53,320
Hurry!

82
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:56,520
Come put out the fire!

83
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:24,910
Hello, Xia Xue.

84
00:15:24,910 --> 00:15:26,840
Come on, let's go play at the beach.

85
00:15:28,910 --> 00:15:31,390
Xia Xue, here's a gift for you.

86
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,440
What do you think

87
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:50,030
we'll be like in ten years?

88
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,200
Ten years from now?

89
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:56,600
I think I'll be pretty busy by then.

90
00:15:57,390 --> 00:15:58,480
But don't worry,

91
00:15:59,270 --> 00:16:02,080
I'll come home on time every night.

92
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:05,510
On weekends, I'll take you out to eat,

93
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:07,240
go shopping, and watch movies.

94
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:09,390
And every year,

95
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:11,390
we'll find time to travel,

96
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:13,790
to all the places you want to visit.

97
00:16:13,910 --> 00:16:14,910
All the places.

98
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,200
Xia Xue!

99
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:22,320
I will love you all my life!

100
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:24,550
I accept that!

101
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:05,810
What's on your mind?

102
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,680
Where's my motorcycle?

103
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:13,920
What's wrong with swapping

104
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,960
that motorcycle for a sports car?

105
00:17:17,240 --> 00:17:18,640
You don't know anything.

106
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,480
This car is the only one
in the entire city.

107
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,810
If I drive it, I'll definitely get caught.

108
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,680
Then,

109
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,200
find a dealer

110
00:17:27,200 --> 00:17:28,800
and sell it as a smuggled car.

111
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:30,200
This car

112
00:17:30,790 --> 00:17:32,320
must be worth a lot of money.

113
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,310
That could work.

114
00:17:36,750 --> 00:17:38,480
But I just don't get it.

115
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:41,010
My motorcycle is missing,

116
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,790
so Ma Kai must have taken it.

117
00:17:43,790 --> 00:17:46,960
But how did he end up
dead at the shipyard?

118
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,770
Who cares where he died?

119
00:17:57,110 --> 00:17:59,550
This car is ours now anyway.

120
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,400
What do you mean "ours"?

121
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,790
It's mine.

122
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,480
Don't tell anyone about the car.

123
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:16,920
No smoking in the car.

124
00:20:04,790 --> 00:20:05,590
Dude,

125
00:20:05,830 --> 00:20:06,550
do you buy smuggled cars?

126
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:07,200
Yes.

127
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:09,240
I buy anything with wheels.

128
00:20:09,440 --> 00:20:10,040
Which one?

129
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:11,960
It's not here.

130
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,350
This kind of car is hard to handle.

131
00:20:15,720 --> 00:20:17,320
You have to let me see the car.

132
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:18,720
Come with me.

133
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:20,000
Okay.

134
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:24,640
What are you doing?

135
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,440
You,

136
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:26,960
come with us.

137
00:20:28,350 --> 00:20:29,270
Who are you?

138
00:20:29,920 --> 00:20:30,440
Mr. Ma

139
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:31,680
invites you for tea.

140
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,750
M-Mr. Ma?

141
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:44,270
Sir,

142
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:45,920
you wanted to see me?

143
00:20:49,270 --> 00:20:50,530
Where are the car keys?

144
00:20:51,920 --> 00:20:53,200
How have you been?

145
00:20:54,680 --> 00:20:55,510
The car keys.

146
00:20:57,270 --> 00:20:58,480
What car keys?

147
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:25,200
Thank you, Mr. Ma.

148
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,400
Sir,

149
00:21:38,590 --> 00:21:40,240
you mean Kai's car?

150
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:42,110
I didn't know which car you meant.

151
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:43,730
Here you are.

152
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:45,400
Wait—

153
00:21:46,790 --> 00:21:47,640
Sir!

154
00:21:47,640 --> 00:21:49,400
Kai... Kai is not dead.

155
00:21:52,110 --> 00:21:53,240
What do you mean?

156
00:21:55,510 --> 00:21:58,350
Kai wasn't at the explosion site that day.

157
00:22:14,030 --> 00:22:14,880
Kai,

158
00:22:16,350 --> 00:22:17,680
what took you so long?

159
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,070
What's wrong?

160
00:22:20,070 --> 00:22:21,070
You look out of it.

161
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,050
I didn't sleep well.

162
00:22:25,590 --> 00:22:26,990
Check my car for me later.

163
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:28,920
What happened to it?

164
00:22:29,510 --> 00:22:31,110
I hit a rabbit on the way here.

165
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:32,470
Wash it.

166
00:22:32,470 --> 00:22:34,070
and check the wheel balance or something.

167
00:22:34,070 --> 00:22:34,920
You got it.

168
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:38,680
Don't smoke in my car.

169
00:22:38,830 --> 00:22:40,160
Of course not.

170
00:22:41,400 --> 00:22:42,160
Kai,

171
00:22:43,030 --> 00:22:46,510
don't forget the workshop's
safety inspection today.

172
00:22:46,590 --> 00:22:47,590
Screw that.

173
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,680
I'll sit for a bit, then go back to sleep.

174
00:22:49,680 --> 00:22:50,750
Wait,

175
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:53,160
the city is cracking down on this.

176
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:54,960
Director Qiu takes it seriously.

177
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,510
Just go sign in and leave.

178
00:22:59,350 --> 00:23:00,240
Did I not sleep well,

179
00:23:00,240 --> 00:23:01,160
or did you?

180
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,540
Do you think I'm afraid of him?

181
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:08,400
I'm afraid he'll snitch to your father.

182
00:23:09,200 --> 00:23:11,110
We just got out of the police station.

183
00:23:11,110 --> 00:23:12,720
If we piss off the old man,

184
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,270
we won't be able to go out and have fun.

185
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:22,040
Give me the motorcycle keys.

186
00:23:22,350 --> 00:23:22,720
Here.

187
00:23:38,480 --> 00:23:39,680
Ride slowly.

188
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:40,480
Yeah.

189
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:50,960
The day of the explosion,
Kai asked me to fix his car.

190
00:23:52,240 --> 00:23:54,510
He rode my motorcycle to the factory.

191
00:23:55,350 --> 00:23:58,550
He said he just wanted to clock in
and then go home to sleep.

192
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:02,680
Then the accident happened at the factory.

193
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,640
I went to the site
to look for my motorcycle.

194
00:24:06,070 --> 00:24:08,400
I looked everywhere but couldn't find it.

195
00:24:10,270 --> 00:24:11,350
I figure,

196
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:14,550
either Kai left before the explosion,

197
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:17,020
or he never went to the factory at all.

198
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:19,460
Anyway, he wasn't at the explosion site.

199
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:22,310
Ma Kai is dead.

200
00:24:25,070 --> 00:24:27,200
And you were looking for a motorcycle?

201
00:24:29,440 --> 00:24:32,770
I went to find Kai and look for
my motorcycle while I was at it.

202
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:34,640
If we find the motorcycle,

203
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:36,240
we will definitely find Kai.

204
00:24:36,240 --> 00:24:38,040
Why didn't you say this earlier?

205
00:24:39,750 --> 00:24:42,350
I wouldn't dare
talk about something this big.

206
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:46,280
It's not that you wouldn't dare.

207
00:24:46,750 --> 00:24:48,510
You're hoping Ma Kai is dead.

208
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:50,750
You just want that car.

209
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:53,960
Sir, I really didn't mean that.

210
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:56,240
I really... I wouldn't dare think that.

211
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:57,720
Sir,

212
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,030
please give me a chance.

213
00:24:59,030 --> 00:25:00,720
I can definitely find Kai.

214
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:05,350
Fine. I'll give you a chance.

215
00:25:09,680 --> 00:25:12,270
If Ma Kai is really still alive,

216
00:25:13,590 --> 00:25:15,270
the car is yours.

217
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:20,270
Hello?

218
00:25:20,510 --> 00:25:22,640
It's Ma Derong. Run a plate for me.

219
00:25:25,110 --> 00:25:26,550
We received a report.

220
00:25:26,550 --> 00:25:27,960
The motorcycle of Ma Kai,

221
00:25:27,960 --> 00:25:29,750
the victim of the shipyard explosion,
is missing.

222
00:25:29,750 --> 00:25:32,240
The license plate number is Ping E57685.

223
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:35,350
Ma Kai's family suspects
he's still alive.

224
00:25:35,350 --> 00:25:36,790
Surveillance shows that

225
00:25:36,790 --> 00:25:38,510
the motorcycle's last known location

226
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:40,110
was halfway up Lover's Peak.

227
00:25:44,070 --> 00:25:46,960
I'll let you keep this hand
for a few days.

228
00:25:49,160 --> 00:25:50,510
Thank you, sir.

229
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:55,720
What's wrong? Why were you looking for me?

230
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,720
A lot of police went to Lover's Peak.

231
00:25:57,920 --> 00:25:58,830
Could they...

232
00:26:00,640 --> 00:26:01,270
Where are you going?

233
00:26:01,270 --> 00:26:02,730
Go wait for me at the plane.

234
00:26:09,110 --> 00:26:11,170
That's right. This is my motorcycle.

235
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:12,450
Are you sure?

236
00:26:12,680 --> 00:26:13,590
I'm sure.

237
00:26:16,720 --> 00:26:18,650
Start a sweeping search. Move out!

238
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,030
Search!

239
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,400
Hello?

240
00:26:43,160 --> 00:26:44,620
I'm still at Lover's Peak.

241
00:26:45,200 --> 00:26:47,350
The area of Lover's Peak is too large,

242
00:26:47,830 --> 00:26:50,510
so the search is indeed difficult.

243
00:26:51,070 --> 00:26:52,750
Please tell the family that we will

244
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:53,950
do our best to search.

245
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:00,590
Report!

246
00:27:00,790 --> 00:27:02,190
We found something here!

247
00:27:06,590 --> 00:27:07,190
Over here.

248
00:27:07,440 --> 00:27:07,830
Here.

249
00:27:24,880 --> 00:27:27,720
Sir, I really didn't lie.

250
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:30,720
I really believe Kai is fine.

251
00:27:31,750 --> 00:27:34,310
I think he's just afraid you'll find out

252
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:37,150
he skipped work
on the day of the explosion,

253
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,750
so he went into hiding.

254
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:47,510
You'd better not
be lying to me about my son.

255
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:50,680
Sir, I wouldn't dare.

256
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:52,110
I wouldn't dare.

257
00:27:56,790 --> 00:27:57,680
Sir,

258
00:27:58,110 --> 00:28:00,590
about the car you promised me...

259
00:28:04,310 --> 00:28:05,110
No rush.

260
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,310
Let's find Kai first.

261
00:28:07,960 --> 00:28:09,030
Find Kai first.

262
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:11,610
I'll get going then.

263
00:28:20,160 --> 00:28:22,160
Have someone keep an eye on that guy.

264
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,240
Lin Hua.

265
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:39,640
Where exactly did you hide the body?

266
00:28:48,680 --> 00:28:49,590
Don't ask.

267
00:28:53,750 --> 00:28:55,610
It's better if you two don't know.

268
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:01,160
What do you mean?

269
00:29:04,830 --> 00:29:07,310
Such a big matter,
did you ever discuss it with us?

270
00:29:07,310 --> 00:29:08,440
Discuss what?

271
00:29:10,110 --> 00:29:12,040
This has nothing to do with you two.

272
00:29:12,750 --> 00:29:13,880
I'll take the blame.

273
00:29:16,070 --> 00:29:17,510
How can you take the blame?

274
00:29:17,510 --> 00:29:18,640
How can you take the blame?

275
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:20,900
If you take the blame,
what about Xia Xue?

276
00:29:26,400 --> 00:29:28,060
Besides, do you have a motive?

277
00:29:30,960 --> 00:29:33,890
You two are college students
with higher education.

278
00:29:34,240 --> 00:29:35,550
Even if you had a conflict with Ma Kai,

279
00:29:35,550 --> 00:29:36,750
would you kill him?

280
00:29:37,720 --> 00:29:39,640
The police just need to ask
around the shipyard,

281
00:29:39,640 --> 00:29:41,750
and they'll know
how Ma Kai usually bullied me.

282
00:29:41,750 --> 00:29:44,010
Who do you think the police will believe?

283
00:29:53,160 --> 00:29:55,360
The police haven't found anything yet.

284
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:57,880
So Ma Kai...

285
00:29:59,640 --> 00:30:01,270
died at the shipyard.

286
00:30:04,310 --> 00:30:05,480
From now on,

287
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:10,210
this has nothing to do with you.

288
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:42,070
Sir,

289
00:30:42,510 --> 00:30:43,910
what happened to the dog?

290
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:45,800
It ate rat poison and died today.

291
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,880
I just buried it,
but the rain washed it out.

292
00:30:47,880 --> 00:30:50,110
I need to dig the pit deeper.

293
00:33:31,310 --> 00:33:32,640
Go play somewhere else.

294
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,070
Stop messing around.

295
00:33:35,590 --> 00:33:37,200
Believe it or not, I'll smash it.

296
00:33:37,200 --> 00:33:38,480
Give it back to me.

297
00:33:42,270 --> 00:33:43,590
Um, I remember our union

298
00:33:43,590 --> 00:33:44,790
has a DV camera, right?

299
00:33:44,790 --> 00:33:46,350
The one used at last year's party.

300
00:33:46,350 --> 00:33:47,590
Can I borrow it?

301
00:33:48,550 --> 00:33:49,750
Where did you get this?

302
00:33:49,750 --> 00:33:51,210
I found it on the mountain.

303
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:09,510
This device is mine.

304
00:34:09,510 --> 00:34:11,310
It has my work unit written on it.

305
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:12,630
Don't play around here.

306
00:34:12,630 --> 00:34:13,510
Go home.

307
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:16,630
What are you doing? I'll kick you.

308
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:17,760
Go home.
